title.narrative: Output 2.1: Early Childhood Development “By 2022, Cross-sectoral ECD policies and standards updated and coordination and management capacities are enhanced.

description.narrative: Cross-sectoral Early Childhood Development (ECD) policies and standards continue to be reinforced, including through an updated situation analysis and the developed framework for national Early Learning and Development Standards. These critical inputs informed the drafting of a national strategy for ECD and are paving the way for an evidence-based ECD action plan. A new National Task Force for ECD Policies has been established and is effectively coordinating ECD priority actions across the government (health, education, social protection), involving civil society organizations, religious leaders, and academia in key analysis and policy related to ECD. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/12/2019
